        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 4:53PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 452 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Simsboro, or 8 miles northeast of Hughes, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
West Memphis, Marion, Hughes, T O Fuller State Park, Memphis, Walls,
Edmondson, Horseshoe Lake, Anthonyville, Jennette, Lake Cormorant,
Simsboro, Pinckney, Crittenden, Browns, Louise, Presidents Island,
Beck, Democrat, and Glover.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
